"rests easily in the shooter's hands, and the focusing lenses automatically "
"correct the user's aim to help bring the beam on target -- and keep it "
"there. It may inflict less damage per shot than its conventional projectile-"
"firing counterparts, but it can do more over time if the shooter keeps the "
"target in his sights. Eight troops with conventional assault rifles firing "
"away at full-auto can easily miss a moving target. With laser rifles, that "
"becomes a near-impossibility.\n"
